The paper discusses synaptic plasticity dynamics in biological models of neurons and neuromorphic hardware, and the use of transfer learning and surrogate gradient few-shot learning on a neuromorphic research processor. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Robotics (cs.RO).
